com.siperian.bdd.userexits.datamodel

Interface CustomizableBDDObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BDDObject

    public interface CustomizableBDDObject
extends BDDObject
    Extended representation of a BDD data object for use in a user exit. In addition to base BDDObject operations provides possibility to manipulate data representation:
    • overwrite value of certain fields
    • disable editing of certain fields
    See Also:
    BDDObject

      • getCustomizableChildren

        List<CustomizableBDDObject> getCustomizableChildren(String childName)
        Returns all child objects with specified name for the current object. Primary object in BDD Configuration can have child objects in accordance to BDD Configuration specification. Children are grouped by child object definitions (one2ManyChild, many2ManyChild ... tags and every child definition has attribute name.
        Parameters:
        childName - - value of name attribute in child definition.
        Returns:
        the list of child objects.
